Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events: A set of three views of what the writer believes to be an Army Day Parade, being reviewed from a stand at the Arsenal in Central Park. View No. 1 shows the marchers passing the dignitaries which include General Pershing (shown in close-up View 2). No. 3 is in a southward direction on Fifth Avenue and shows Legonaires and Junior Units approaching the reviewing stand. In this instance Sixty-third Street is to the left and Central Park on the right.

About, 1925?

No. 1 East 63rd Street, adjoining the N.E. corner of Fifth Avenue, showing a 4 story brownstone residence. To the right is a similar structure, No. 3, which is the property of Grace Wilson. The 12 story apartment house on the left is No. 820 - Fifth Avenue and is of particular interest because of its 18 room suites. Occupants here in December 1937, included Alfred P. Sloan, Alfred E.
